{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We use the base model EfficientNet-B0 to compute features on single-cell crops of 128 × 128 pixels.",
    "It consists of 9 stages: input, seven inverted residual convolutional blocks from MobileNetV2 49 (with the addition of squeeze and excitation optimization) and final layers.",
    "The usage of convolutional blocks from MobileNetV2 in combination with neural architecture search gave EfficientNet an advantage in terms of computational efficiency and accuracy compared to ResNet50.",
    "This model has only 4 million parameters and can extract features from single cells in a few milliseconds using GPU acceleration.",
    "EfficientNet has been previously used for image-based profiling, including in models trained with the CytoImageNet dataset 50, by top competitors in the Recursion Cellular Image Classification challenge in Kaggle, and for studying variants of unknown significance in cancer lung cells 10."
  ],
